<problem id="fs-idp93155376">
<para id="fs-idp580400">A molecule with the formula AB<sub>3</sub> could have one of four different shapes. Give the shape and the hybridization of the central A atom for each.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idp51460320">
<para id="fs-idm14765376">trigonal planar, <emphasis effect="italics">sp</emphasis><sup>2</sup>; trigonal pyramidal (one lone pair on A) <emphasis effect="italics">sp</emphasis><sup>3</sup>; T-shaped (two lone pairs on A <emphasis effect="italics">sp</emphasis><sup>3</sup><emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis>, or (three lone pairs on A) <emphasis effect="italics">sp</emphasis><sup>3</sup><emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis><sup>2</sup></para>
